==English==

===Etymology===
Since 16th century, from Greek ''epilepsia'', from ''[[epi-]]'', upon, + ''lepsis'', attack, seizure

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''epilepsy''' (''plural'' '''epilepsies''')

# {{pathology}} A medical [[condition]] in which the sufferer experiences [[seizure]]s (or [[convulsion]]s) and [[blackout]]s.

